Description: Street Jelly Media is an online platform where musicians perform live online through webcam and computer.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: StreetJelly.com is online busking: video streaming LIVE musicians performing by webcam for tips.   Musicians, singer / songwriters, vocalists, and all types perform in their living rooms, basements, home studios, where ever with a computer and webcam.  Music Lovers watch and chat with the artists, much like in a chat room.  The viewers purchase virtual tokens which they use as currency to tip the musicians.  Viewers can also use their tokens towards awards, Rocker Pins, to give to the artists.  The musicians then cash out their tokens for real money, sent via PayPal. StreetJelly is about people, musicians actually. Take “LanaEve,” for instance, who performs often on StreetJelly.  She’s a teenage prodigy from Nashville.  Despite this sounding like a cliche, she really has the voice of an angel.  Want to see the most genuine happy smile?  Say “hello” to her and drop her a token.  Then there’s “Maestro” from Seattle, an accomplished musician and music teacher from School of Rock.  Maestro will draw you in with his soothing piano and guitar originals.  Before you know it, time has flown by and your day is much better.  There’s also folk music duo Rick and Denise called “Amaranth.” They put on weekly shows from their home for friends and family around the country.  You’ll feel like you are with family having warm milk and cookies when witnessing their “house concerts.” There are so many more stories, but that's the idea.  StreetJelly brings music lovers in touch with real musicians, in real time, in all its raw musical goodness.  Try that with a digital download!
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Events, Hardware, Information Technology, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Messaging and Telecommunications, Music and Audio, Video

Description: Bookerville is a provider of a fully featured vacation rental software.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Bookerville provides vacation rental property management software for vacation rental owners, vacation rental property managers and bed and breakfast owners. Our SaaS helps our customers manage their rentals, organize their bookings, communicate with guests in a professional way, and streamline their management tasks. Bookerville’s software is flexible and customizable in order to meet the wide range of needs of our clients. We are small and adept; we respond quickly to the ever changing needs of the vacation rental industry and the ideas submitted to us by our customers. Bookerville software allows customers to manage reservations and availability, communicate with guests, manage housekeeping, integrate "widgets" into their websites, and automatically respond to inquiries from external vacation rental portals. Customers and their guests enjoy commission-free bookings. International customers can show rates in their choice of currency. Managers can customize email templates, automatically send emails based on scheduled dates, synchronize with external availability calendars, track advertising channels, manage multiple users with varying levels of access, and manage all the details and ongoing communications associated with the stream of incoming rental inquiries. Guests can see availability, price out their stay before committing, request a booking, or book directly online if you want them to.  Bookerville also supports contract  management,  full reporting and export of data, integrated payments into your own account, and housekeeping automation. Our mission: Bookerville is dedicated to creating clever, easy-to-use vacation rental management software. By keeping in touch with the industry, we aim to surprise and delight our customers by providing technology-based solutions that actually help them run their business the way they want. Founded in 2009, Bookerville is a Virginia-based software company.

Desi Hits! aims to make South Asian culture more widely dispersed and understood as well as offering a platform for South Asian artists to promote themselves globally. Desi Hits! draws on the multicultural backgrounds of our target audience, namely the â€œDesiâ€, who can often be described as bilingual, trendy, cosmopolitan and as likely to jive to Madonna as they are to Bollywood. We focus heavily on bi-cultural remixes as they uniquely represent the next generation (and beyond) South Asian experience. Itâ€™s an exciting time for the South Asian community, particularly as the cross pollination of cultural heritage is spilling into the mainstream. Icons such as Aishwarya Rai and pop idols such as M.I.A. point to a new hybrid pop vernacular that represents South Asians everywhere. The impact on global pop can be seen by the fact that artists such as Britney Spears, Madonna, Jay-Z and Timbaland have put a South Asian spin to their music and are working with Desi producers and artists. The Desi Hits! offering, however, is not exclusively South Asian. Desi Hits! covers mainstream as well as bicultural news, music, interviews and lifestyle content with a global perspective since the next generation Desi wants it all and is currently forced to go to multiple vendors to get it. To that end, Desi Hits! will just as soon cover Usher and P Diddy as it would up and coming South Asian artists like Jay Sean and Rishi Rich or even Bollywood.
